Author: Elisa Novick
Content: -Cheryl Fritz Inspiring but... I think you are a bit understating how much time it takes to prepare, and clean up after juicing. 💜🫙

Author: Cheryl Fritz
Content: --Elisa Novick My inexpensive magic buy comes apart in seconds..... Cleaning & rinse, a minute, the celery ( cutting, washing, juicing  takes a minute.  I'm 70 & very efficient,  I can't speak for  you.

Author: Elisa Novick
Content: --Cheryl Fritz Nutribullets, if that is what you are referring to, don't extract the juice. According to AW, we don't want any pulp in the juice.

Author: Cheryl Fritz
Content:
--Elisa Novick This is a nutribullet juicer.....
Please educate yourself.
It extracts juice, hence  pulp is collected in the side shute.
Takes seconds, no heat is created.
I had a $350 juicer decades ago and abandoned juicing due to the complexity....
Proof of extraction is in my posted comment, with juice in the glass.
I've followed AW for decades, what do you need to say now ??
